.TH "hfi1_rcd_get_by_index" 9 "hfi1_rcd_get_by_index" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hfi1_rcd_get_by_index \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hfi1_ctxtdata *" hfi1_rcd_get_by_index
.BI "(struct hfi1_devdata *dd "  ","
.BI "u16 ctxt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dd" 12
pointer to a valid devdata structure
.IP "ctxt" 12
the index of an possilbe rcd
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
We need to protect access to the rcd array.  If access is needed to
one or more index, get the protecting spinlock and then increment the
kref.

The caller is responsible for making the \fB_put\fP.
